commentary: Santner to Sabbir Rahman, 1 wide, OUT stumping appeal down leg side as Sabbir slips attempting a sweep. Lost his footing...and he is short as he looks to get the back bat in. That's unfortunate. It's a length ball down leg. His front heel slips on the surface as he chases this. He's in a tangle with both feet out of the crease and his body on the floor. Panic as he looks to sweep the bat along the ground and into the crease. Latham's taken some time with that stumping, but there's enough going against Sabbir for him to be marginally short

commentary: Santner to Mehidy Hasan Miraz, OUT Santner wins the battle! They're both intelligent cricketers, Santner and Mehidy. Mehidy's footwork was top-class so far and he was maneuvering Santner all over and picking him off. Almost as a pattern, all of Santner's sixth balls were quicker, but this time he hangs it up wide outside off on a length. Mehidy wants to sweep to the backward square boundary after shuffling, but his top-edge is easy for short fine to get to with a jog to the left. Neesham there
